1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:04,000
Welcome to the Example Subtitle File!

2
00:00:04,000 --> 00:00:08,000
This is a demonstration of SRT subtitles.

3
00:00:08,000 --> 00:00:12,000
You can use SRT files to add subtitles to your videos.

4
00:00:12,000 --> 00:00:16,000
Each subtitle entry consists of a number, a timecode, and the subtitle text.

5
00:00:16,000 --> 00:00:20,000
The timecode format is hours:minutes:seconds,milliseconds.

6
00:00:20,000 --> 00:00:24,000
You can adjust the timing to match your video.

7
00:00:24,000 --> 00:00:28,000
Make sure the subtitle text is clear and readable.

8
00:00:28,000 --> 00:00:32,000
Keep your subtitles short and easy to understand.

9
00:00:32,000 --> 00:00:36,000
Avoid placing too much text on the screen at once.

10
00:00:36,000 --> 00:00:40,000
Sync the subtitles carefully with the spoken audio.

11
00:00:40,000 --> 00:00:44,000
Review your subtitles before publishing your video.

12
00:00:44,000 --> 00:00:48,000
Good subtitles improve viewer engagement.

13
00:00:48,000 --> 00:00:52,000
They also make your content accessible to a wider audience.

14
00:00:52,000 --> 00:00:56,000
Now you know the basics of creating an SRT file.

15
00:00:56,000 --> 00:01:00,000
Enjoy adding subtitles to your videos!